HTML forms, covering everything from basic form creation to building complex and interactive forms. 
we'll learn how to create form elements, handle form submissions, and validate user input.
We'll explore various form elements such as text inputs, checkboxes, radio buttons, select dropdowns, and more. 
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
CODE
..............................
(formone.html)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Event Registration</h2>
    <form>
        <label for="name1">Name:</label>
        <input type="text" name="name" id="name1">
        <br>
        <br>
        <label for="Email1">Email</label>
        <input type="text" class="Email" id="Email1">
        <br>
        <br>
        <label for="phone">Phone</label>
        <input type="tele" class="phone" id="phone">
        <br>
        <br>
                <label for="occ">Language Know</label>
                <select name="occupution" id="occ">
                    <option value="HTML">HTML</option>
                    <option value="css">CSS</option>
                    <option value="java-script">JAVA-SCRIPT</option>
                </select>
                <br>
                <br>
                <fieldset>
                    <legend>
                        <label for="Topics">Topics of Interst</label>
                        <br>
                        <label for="html">HTML</label>
                        <input type="checkbox" name="html" id="html">
                        <label for="css">CSS</label>
                        <input type="checkbox" name="css" id="css">
                        <label for="java">Java</label>
                        <input type="checkbox" name="java" id="Java">
                    </legend>
                </fieldset>
                <br>
                <br>
                <label for="comm">Comments:</label>
                <br>
                <textarea name="comment" id="comm" cols="30" rows="10"></textarea>

                <button>Register</button>
            

    </form>
    
</body>
</html>
